LEX Escrow.
COMMENT: %ERR

"Payer" is a person.
"Payee" is a person.
"Arbiter" is a person.
"Fee" is an amount.

The Payer pays an amount into escrow, appoints the Payee, appoints the Arbiter, and fixes the Fee.

CLAUSE: Pay Out.
The Arbiter or the Payer may pay from escrow the Fee to themselves, and afterwards pay the remainder of the escrow to the Payee.

CLAUSE: Pay Back.
The Arbiter may pay from escrow the Fee to themselves, and afterwards return the remainder of the escrow to the Payer.

